title: Art - the way it is (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
Prentice-Hall | 1973 | 348 pag | Eng | Pdf | ISBN 0130492213 | 41 MB

The Way It Is brims with dramatic contrasts: the Renaissance and the twentieth century, religious art and Dada, Caravaggio and Norman Rockwell.

Through such juxtapositions a remarkably broad vision emerges as the reader learns to separate the incidental from the essential, the ephemeral from the permanent, and
thus to discriminate between styles, movements, and periods
